09/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A two-day regional conference on the development of Albania-Macedonia relations wrapped up Sunday (8 December) in Ohrid.
The conference reviewed the common goal of NATO membership and underscored the need to better understand the problems of the Albanian minority in Macedonia and the Macedonian minority in Albania.
Participants agreed that there is room for improvement, especially in regards to strengthening ties between the border crime prevention units.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 09/12/02;
MIA, A1 TV - 08/12/02)
